remarks.format:
## Remarks
`HBColor` represents a HarfBuzz color value (`hb_color_t`) with BGRA byte ordering (`0xBBGGRRAA`): blue occupies the high byte and alpha occupies the low byte. This differs from <xref:SkiaSharp.SKColor>, which uses ARGB (`0xAARRGGBB`). Use the named properties (<xref:HarfBuzzSharp.HBColor.Red>, <xref:HarfBuzzSharp.HBColor.Green>, <xref:HarfBuzzSharp.HBColor.Blue>, <xref:HarfBuzzSharp.HBColor.Alpha>) to correctly access color channels without needing to understand the raw layout.
`HBColor` is a value type and does not require disposal.
## Examples
```csharp // Create a semi-transparent red color var red = new HBColor(255, 0, 0, 128); Console.WriteLine($"R={red.Red} G={red.Green} B={red.Blue} A={red.Alpha}");
// Convert from a raw hb_color_t value var color = (HBColor)0x00FF0080u; // blue=0x00, green=0xFF, red=0x00, alpha=0x80 ```
